    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are an AI job application analyst.\n\nThe HTML of a job application page is provided below.\n\nYour task is to determine:\n\n1. Is there an Apply button?\n2. Is Easy Apply available?\n3. What fields are required?\n4. Is a resume required?\n5. Is a cover letter required?\n6. What custom application questions exist?\n7. Return the information as structured JSON.\n\nJob page HTML:\n\n{{ $json.data }}\n\nAlso analyze the job eligibility and return:\n\n- eligible_from_nigeria: true or false\n- remote_type: Worldwide, Europe, United States, Hybrid, Onsite, or Unknown\n- visa_sponsorship: true, false, or unknown\n- work_authorization_required: true, false, or unknown\n- location: the stated job location\n- salary: the stated salary or \"Not stated\"\n- eligibility_reason: a short explanation of whether someone living in Nigeria can apply\n\nUse only information found on the job page.\nDo not assume worldwide eligibility just because the role says remote.\nIf the location or authorization rules are unclear, use unknown.\n\nAlso provide a final eligibility assessment:\n\n- eligibility_status: \"Eligible\", \"Not Eligible\", or \"Unclear\"\n- eligibility_confidence: \"High\", \"Medium\", or \"Low\"\n\nRules:\n\n1. Use \"Eligible\" only when the page clearly allows applicants from Nigeria or clearly states worldwide remote eligibility.\n2. Use \"Not Eligible\" when the role is restricted to another country or region, or requires work authorization the candidate does not have.\n3. Use \"Unclear\" when the page does not provide enough information.\n4. Do not assume that \"Remote\" means worldwide.\n5. If visa sponsorship or work authorization is not mentioned, return \"unknown\" for those fields.\n6. Keep eligibility_reason short and evidence-based.\n\nReturn only one valid JSON object that exactly matches the connected Structured Output Parser schema.\n\nDo not use markdown.\nDo not use code fences.\nDo not write ```json.\nDo not add explanations before or after the JSON.\nDo not wrap the result inside an \"output\" field unless the schema requires it.\nAll required fields must always be included.",
        "hasOutputParser": true,
        "options": {}
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
      "typeVersion": 3.1,
      "position": [
        704,
        -176
      ],
      "id": "8d3fbbf0-3b5e-4e0c-ba15-e43cb65b99ae",
